{"_id":"13DeJLCfm7zgAdRW","name":"Invoke Obitue-Que","permission":{"default":0,"U5X07uKi3FMVWkQ1":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.dcc-compendiums.dcc-spell-tables.9A1VQD83v8bwbnai"}},"img":"modules/dcc-core-book/assets/svg/game-icons-net/ceremonial-mask.svg","description":"<h1>Invoke Obitue-Que</h1><p><strong>Level:</strong> 1</p><p><strong>Range:</strong> Self</p><p><strong>Duration:</strong> Varies</p><p><strong>Casting Time:</strong> 1 round, and the spell may be cast only a limited number of times, according to results of patron bond.</p><p><strong>Save:</strong> None</p><p><strong>Page:</strong> 355</p><br><p>The Lord of the Five is a pit fiend and balor general whose experimental mutations gave him five ruby-red eyes. His physical form was defeated by a line of noble barbarians but his dominating spirit survives in areas of blight and decay, where his ceremonies are performed. He demands that his subjects pursue his cryptic agenda of conquest. He is fast to respond to invocations, but the aid he sends may dominate the caster as much as aid him.</p><br><p><strong>Spell Data:</strong> @Compendium[dcc-core-book.dcc-core-spell-journals.Invoke Obitue-Que]{Invoke Obitue-Que}</p>","results":[{"_id":"iNBPUJVD5kVtmUWW","flags":{},"type":0,"text":"Lost, failure, and worse! Roll [[/roll 1d6]] modified by Luck: (3 or less) corruption + patron taint; (4-5) corruption; (6+) patron taint.","img":"icons/svg/d20-black.svg","resultId":"","weight":1,"range":[-99,1],"drawn":false},{"_id":"WN3fmvaIVtNAHEwO","flags":{},"type":0,"text":"Failure. Unlike other spells, invoke patron may not be lost for the day. Depending on the results of patron bond, the wizard may still be able to cast it.","img":"icons/svg/d20-black.svg","resultId":"","weight":1,"range":[2,11],"drawn":false},{"_id":"PyPz7oWdXMlDQeyF","flags":{},"type":0,"text":"Blight. All plants within 100’ of the caster wither and die. All living creatures in range (excluding allies and the caster) grow suddenly weak, losing [[/roll 1d4]] Strength for the next hour.","img":"icons/svg/d20-black.svg","resultId":"","weight":1,"range":[12,13],"drawn":false},{"_id":"9j8IyYzy8BwnSljI","flags":{},"type":0,"text":"Blight blade. The caster’s weapon of choice (including staff or rod, as appropriate) grows black and dusky. Until the next sunrise, any creature struck by the blighted blade must make a DC 16 Fort save or be poisoned with a terrible blight that causes the permanent loss of [[/roll 1d4]] Strength.","img":"icons/svg/d20-black.svg","resultId":"","weight":1,"range":[14,17],"drawn":false},{"_id":"VsxX3dEpaQMnOKZd","flags":{},"type":0,"text":"Eldritch flames. The caster’s body crackles with red flames, which give off no heat but are clearly visible. The flames grant a +6 bonus to attack rolls for the next turn, and whenever the caster attacks, they swirl above him and form the face of Obitu-Que, who sneers in profane delight.","img":"icons/svg/d20-black.svg","resultId":"","weight":1,"range":[18,19],"drawn":false},{"_id":"HyHjuNDG7pLwc0RI","flags":{},"type":0,"text":"Pit flames. The caster suffers 1 hp of damage as a bolt of black flame, jets from the ground through his body and arcs toward the nearest enemy. That enemy suffers [[/roll 2d6]] damage immediately and another [[/roll 1d6]] damage from burns on the following round.","img":"icons/svg/d20-black.svg","resultId":"","weight":1,"range":[20,23],"drawn":false},{"_id":"vBh85PGyvdOgQO7p","flags":{},"type":0,"text":"Dominance. The demon’s will surges into the caster’s mind and from it to his nearest enemy. The caster loses [[/roll 1d4]] points of Personality for the next hour and feels irresistible compulsions to further Obitu-Que’s agenda (at the judge’s discretion). <br /><br />One designated enemy within 100’ must make a DC 24 Will save or be dominated for [[/roll 1d6]] turns. While dominated, the caster controls the enemy’s every action but must concentrate to do so. If the caster stops concentrating, the dominated enemy simply stands silent and immobile like a zombie.","img":"icons/svg/d20-black.svg","resultId":"","weight":1,"range":[24,27],"drawn":false},{"_id":"mozW31gvQUIeu9XK","flags":{},"type":0,"text":"As result 24-27, but the enemy must make a DC 28 Will save.","img":"icons/svg/d20-black.svg","resultId":"","weight":1,"range":[28,29],"drawn":false},{"_id":"tGKddXImJWLl5gpw","flags":{},"type":0,"text":"The five-eyed skull of Obitu-Que appears above the caster, sheathed in the ruby flames of Hell. It remains for five rounds, during which time the caster may cast no other spell. Each round, starting immediately (i.e., in the round of the spell-casting), the caster may direct one eye to dominate any enemy within 100’. The target must make a DC 30 Will save or be dominated. <br /><br />The domination lasts for [[/roll 1d4]] rounds past the end of the round following the disappearance of the skull. The caster controls the actions of all dominated creatures but must concentrate to do so. If the caster stops concentrating, the dominated enemies simply stand silent and immobile like zombies. When the effect ends, the caster temporarily loses [[/roll 1d4]] points of Personality and must follow the will of Obitu-Que for the next hour.","img":"icons/svg/d20-black.svg","resultId":"","weight":1,"range":[30,31],"drawn":false},{"_id":"eNec1wVSpQthYFld","flags":{},"type":0,"text":"As result 30-31, but the enemy must make a DC 32 Will save.","img":"icons/svg/d20-black.svg","resultId":"","weight":1,"range":[32,99],"drawn":false}],"formula":"1d20","replacement":true,"displayRoll":true}
{"_id":"5RHGsjr7N1UmCj1U","name":"Invoke Azi Dahaka","permission":{"default":0,"wWErSsSXezizF0nw":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"RollTable.zTrK8T7IZ4cOA7jK"}},"img":"modules/dcc-core-book/assets/svg/game-icons-net/whirlwind.svg","description":"<h1>Invoke Azi Dahaka</h1><p><strong>Level:</strong> 1</p><p><strong>Range:</strong> Self</p><p><strong>Duration:</strong> Varies</p><p><strong>Casting Time:</strong> 1 round, and the spell may be cast only a limited number of times, according to results of patron bond.</p><p><strong>Save:</strong> None</p><p><strong>Page:</strong> 330</p><br><p>The demon prince of storms and waste, Azi Dahaka is anything but subtle. He is the blasting sand storm, the deadly asp, and the desiccated corpse in scorching sun. He appears as an infernal hydra and expects his followers to bring ruin wherever they go. Eventually the world shall be a desert over which he will rule. His ceremony must be conducted in a desert at high noon where the caster has imbibed no liquid for one day and one night before. He demands much of his followers, causing them to be dehydrated and experience heat-induced visions where he gives them minor quests related to spreading chaos.</p><br><p><strong>Spell Data:</strong> @Compendium[dcc-core-book.dcc-core-spell-journals.Invoke Azi Dahaka]{Invoke Azi Dahaka}</p>","results":[{"_id":"VK4Vltici44uMg75","flags":{},"type":0,"text":"Lost, failure, and worse! Roll [[/roll 1d6]] modified by Luck: (3 or less) corruption + patron taint; (4-5) corruption; (6+) patron taint.","img":"icons/svg/d20-black.svg","resultId":"","weight":1,"range":[-99,1],"drawn":false},{"_id":"MuHAiGh5nLt4tT3T","flags":{},"type":0,"text":"Failure. Unlike other spells, invoke patron may not be lost for the day. Depending on the results of patron bond, the wizard may still be able to cast it.","img":"icons/svg/d20-black.svg","resultId":"","weight":1,"range":[2,11],"drawn":false},{"_id":"L5KHuk8G7d3ytjHw","flags":{},"type":0,"text":"Azi Dahaka sends a bolt of static lightning toward one of the caster’s enemies, causing [[/roll 2d6]] damage (DC 15 Fort save for half). The caster can designate any target within 100’.","img":"icons/svg/d20-black.svg","resultId":"","weight":2,"range":[12,13],"drawn":false},{"_id":"mOtZWzJJiUkrsHbj","flags":{},"type":0,"text":"A cyclone erupts around the caster’s enemies. The caster and his allies are unaffected, but all other creatures within a 30’ radius of the caster suffer [[/roll 1d8]] points of abrasion damage per round. Additionally, each round, all enemies within the cyclone must make a Reflex save or be knocked prone by the storming winds. The cyclone continues for [[/roll 1d4]]+CL rounds.","img":"icons/svg/d20-black.svg","resultId":"","weight":4,"range":[14,17],"drawn":false},{"_id":"ogzRRtfnRcX9pYUr","flags":{},"type":0,"text":"A sandstorm fills the air with blinding dust. However, the caster and his allies can still see normally. Enemies within a 60’ radius are blinded as long as the caster continues to concentrate, for up to 1 minute.","img":"icons/svg/d20-black.svg","resultId":"","weight":2,"range":[18,19],"drawn":false},{"_id":"2PDSFXuJRbuBg1XB","flags":{},"type":0,"text":"A diminutive asp slithers forth from the caster’s sleeve to coil around his hand. The asp will bite any enemy the caster touches until it vanishes in 1 minute. The caster must make a melee attack roll, but the asp grants a +4 bonus. The attack roll can involve a normal melee attack; i.e., the caster could stab with a dagger, and the asp would also make its bite attempt. <br /><br />Any enemy struck by the caster’s melee attacks while the asp is present suffers from a terrible poison. The bite automatically does 1 point of damage the first round, then the poison sets in, automatically causing 2 points on the second round. On each subsequent round the target must make a DC20 Fort save or the damage doubles: potentially 4 points on the third round, then 8 points, then 16 points, and so on. The damage continues doubling until the target makes a Fort save.","img":"icons/svg/d20-black.svg","resultId":"","weight":4,"range":[20,23],"drawn":false},{"_id":"ErpYG9pQHJfwzUjs","flags":{},"type":0,"text":"Azi Dahaka sends a tangled mass of slithering snakes. The hissing swarm arrives in [[/roll 1d3]] rounds. The swarm occupies a space of 30’ x 30’ and attacks all enemies within that space. The individual snakes disperse after 1 minute. <br /><br />Snake swarm: Init +0; Atk bite +2 melee against all in 30’ x 30’ space (dmg [[/roll 1d6]] plus DC 20 Fort save or additional [[/roll 1d6]] points of poison damage); AC 12; HP 60; MV 30’; Act [[/roll 1d20]] (attack all enemies in space); SV Fort +2, Ref +2, Will +0; AL C.","img":"icons/svg/d20-black.svg","resultId":"","weight":4,"range":[24,27],"drawn":false},{"_id":"auPMamUEIFmHoyFK","flags":{},"type":0,"text":"Azi Dahaka sends a brawny three-headed snake to aid his follower. It arrives in [[/roll 1d3]] rounds. The 20’ long creature obeys the caster’s commands for 1 minute, then slithers away. <br /><br />Three-headed snake: Init +6; Atk bite +12 melee (dmg [[/roll 2d8]] plus DC 24 Fort save or additional [[/roll 3d6]] points of poison damage); AC 16; HP 24; MV 30’; Act [[/roll 3d20]]; SV Fort +2, Ref +4, Will +0; AL C.","img":"icons/svg/d20-black.svg","resultId":"","weight":2,"range":[28,29],"drawn":false},{"_id":"wNmkNiMTE8t9uN1b","flags":{},"type":0,"text":"A spectral hydra shimmers into existence like a mirage above the sands. Its seven heads bite and breathe flame on the caster’s enemies before vanishing on the following round. The caster may immediately direct seven attacks to any targets within 60’ of himself. Each attack is either a bite (+10 attack, [[/roll 4d6]] damage) or a fiery breath weapon (+15 attack, [[/roll 2d6]] damage plus DC 20 Ref save or target catches fire, suffering additional [[/roll 2d6]] damage each round until the target makes a DC 20 Ref save).","img":"icons/svg/d20-black.svg","resultId":"","weight":2,"range":[30,31],"drawn":false},{"_id":"wtCMEyu055vbW7Gs","flags":{},"type":0,"text":"Azi Dahaka sends a spectral hydra, as above, which lasts for [[/roll 1d4]]+CL rounds. The caster may direct 7 attacks on each round it remains. The caster must concentrate to direct these attacks","img":"icons/svg/d20-black.svg","resultId":"","weight":1,"range":[32,99],"drawn":false}],"formula":"1d20","replacement":true,"displayRoll":true}
{"_id":"7MrEifa6M0Z6WVoM","name":"Sequester","permission":{"default":0,"U5X07uKi3FMVWkQ1":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.dcc-compendium.spell-tables.rxJV1F2MP6xPrRx9"}},"img":"modules/dcc-core-book/assets/svg/game-icons-net/padlock.svg","description":"<h1>Sequester</h1><p><strong>Level:</strong> 1</p><p><strong>Range:</strong> Varies</p><p><strong>Duration:</strong> [[/roll 1d24]] hours per CL</p><p><strong>Casting Time:</strong> 1 turn</p><p><strong>Save:</strong> Will or Skill check vs. spell check</p><p><strong>Page:</strong> 339</p><br><p>The Path of the Old One requires absolute attention and dedication. The caster secures an area against intrusion, permitting reflection and study so that he can plot his next move.</p><br><p><strong>Spell Data:</strong> @Compendium[dcc-core-book.dcc-core-spell-journals.Sequester]{Sequester}</p>","results":[{"_id":"DCL1s3tnjDc8g1tX","flags":{},"type":0,"text":"Lost, failure, and patron taint.","img":"icons/svg/d20-black.svg","resultId":"","weight":1,"range":[-99,1],"drawn":false},{"_id":"wqr8OloCFvYfQxBW","flags":{},"type":0,"text":"Lost. Failure.","img":"icons/svg/d20-black.svg","resultId":"","weight":10,"range":[2,11],"drawn":false},{"_id":"e4BscOpSKDaHroqA","flags":{},"type":0,"text":"The caster secures an area up to 100 square feet in size. Doors and windows are magically sealed, requiring a DC 15 Pick Locks check to open. The caster is instantly alerted to any being entering the warded area.","img":"icons/svg/d20-black.svg","resultId":"","weight":2,"range":[12,13],"drawn":false},{"_id":"SwLNKZmiAtpk6DGE","flags":{},"type":0,"text":"The caster secures an area up to 500 square feet in size. Doors and windows are magically sealed, requiring a DC 15 Pick Locks check or a password to open. The caster can declare up to 2 portals magically trapped (Find/Disable Traps DC 15; [[/roll 1d10]]+CL fire damage). The caster is instantly alerted to any being entering the warded area.","img":"icons/svg/d20-black.svg","resultId":"","weight":4,"range":[14,17],"drawn":false},{"_id":"3I4mOGiwh3KR2Py0","flags":{},"type":0,"text":"The caster secures an area up to 1,000 square feet in size. Doors and windows are magically sealed, requiring a DC 18 Pick Locks check or a password to open. Lesser doors and windows are treated as stout wood for purposes of destruction (15 hp). The caster can declare up to 4 portals trapped (Find/Disable Traps DC 18; [[/roll 1d12]]+CL fire damage). The caster is instantly alerted to any being entering the area.","img":"icons/svg/d20-black.svg","resultId":"","weight":2,"range":[18,19],"drawn":false},{"_id":"qSgjs0ggdRdaLdxe","flags":{},"type":0,"text":"The caster secures an area up to 3,000 square feet in size. Doors and windows are magically sealed, requiring a DC 20 Pick Locks check or a password to open. Lesser doors and windows are treated as iron bound for purposes of destruction (30 hp). <br /><br />The caster can declare up to 6 portals trapped (Find/ Disable Traps DC 18; [[/roll 1d14]]+CL fire damage) and place a single pit trap up to 20' in depth (Find Traps DC 18). The caster is instantly alerted to any being entering the area.","img":"icons/svg/d20-black.svg","resultId":"","weight":4,"range":[20,23],"drawn":false},{"_id":"LriTiUefho49ApFB","flags":{},"type":0,"text":"The caster secures an area up to 6,000 square feet in size. Doors and windows are magically sealed, requiring a DC 20 Pick Locks check or a password to open. Lesser doors and windows are treated as iron for purposes of destruction (60 hp). <br /><br />The caster can declare up to 8 portals trapped (Find/ Disable Traps DC 20; [[/roll 1d20]]+CL fire damage) and place 4 pit traps up to 40' in depth (Find Traps DC 20). The caster is instantly alerted to any being entering the area.","img":"icons/svg/d20-black.svg","resultId":"","weight":4,"range":[24,27],"drawn":false},{"_id":"YxJ82pMcgNCNuD10","flags":{},"type":0,"text":"The caster secures an area up to 10,000 square feet in size. Doors and windows are magically sealed, requiring a DC 20 Pick Locks check or a password to open. Lesser doors and windows are treated as iron for purposes of destruction (60 hp). <br /><br />The caster can declare up to 8 portals trapped (Find/ Disable Traps DC 20; [[/roll 1d24]]+CL fire damage) and place 4 pit traps up to 60' in depth (Find Traps DC 20). The caster and his allies within the sequestered area are immune to scrying, summoning or teleportation. The caster and his allies are alerted to any being entering the area.","img":"icons/svg/d20-black.svg","resultId":"","weight":2,"range":[28,29],"drawn":false},{"_id":"sTNLv4ge6b4iAR1X","flags":{},"type":0,"text":"(same as 28-29) .. The caster secures an area up to 10,000 square feet in size. Doors and windows are magically sealed, requiring a DC 20 Pick Locks check or a password to open. Lesser doors and windows are treated as iron for purposes of destruction (60 hp). <br /><br />The caster can declare up to 8 portals trapped (Find/ Disable Traps DC 20; [[/roll 1d24]]+CL fire damage) and place 4 pit traps up to 60' in depth (Find Traps DC 20). The caster and his allies within the sequestered area are immune to scrying, summoning or teleportation. The caster and his allies are alerted to any being entering the area.","img":"icons/svg/d20-black.svg","resultId":"","weight":2,"range":[30,31],"drawn":false},{"_id":"QApcWCHZp7clL38z","flags":{},"type":0,"text":"The caster secures any single structure (a keep, tower, palace, dungeon, etc.) regardless of size. Doors and windows are magically sealed, requiring a DC 20 Pick Locks check or a password to open. Lesser doors and windows are treated as iron for purposes of destruction (60 hp). <br /><br />The caster can declare up to 8 portals trapped (Find/ Disable Traps DC 20; [[/roll 1d24]]+CL fire damage), place 4 pit traps that teleport victims to an oubliette 100 miles distant (Find Traps DC 20), and a troop of 50 suits of animated armor (treat as skeletons that cannot be turned). The caster and his allies within the sequestered area are immune to scrying, summoning or teleportation. The caster and his allies are alerted to any being entering the area.","img":"icons/svg/d20-black.svg","resultId":"","weight":68,"range":[32,99],"drawn":false}],"formula":"1d20","replacement":true,"displayRoll":true}
{"_id":"A97otTGdDn4oUhG4","name":"Glorious Mire","permission":{"default":0,"U5X07uKi3FMVWkQ1":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.dcc-compendium.spell-tables.Ohl0bDEKaOtSLSLF"}},"img":"modules/dcc-core-book/assets/svg/game-icons-net/swamp.svg","description":"<h1>Glorious Mire</h1><p><strong>Level:</strong> 2</p><p><strong>Range:</strong> Touch</p><p><strong>Duration:</strong> Varies</p><p><strong>Casting Time:</strong> 1 round</p><p><strong>Save:</strong> None</p><p><strong>Page:</strong> 326</p><br><p>The demon lord of amphibians is most comfortable in the endless swamplands of his home plane. These pits of briny mud extend endlessly toward a low brown horizon, entangled in roots and sunk amidst stiff gray plants and furry mildewed ruins. With this spell, the caster transforms his immediate surroundings into the swampland that Bobugbubilz calls home. Stone floors soften and change to mud, trees destabilize and wobble on their newly liquid foundation, and castles sink into the mire. At low levels the caster can affect only a small volume of space, but at high levels, this spell can bring down castles.</p><br><p><strong>Spell Data:</strong> @Compendium[dcc-core-book.dcc-core-spell-journals.Glorious Mire]{Glorious Mire}</p>","results":[{"_id":"wplweqFoQwnrNAHF","flags":{},"type":0,"text":"Lost, failure, and patron taint.","img":"icons/svg/d20-black.svg","resultId":"","weight":1,"range":[-99,1],"drawn":false},{"_id":"F50IRYPg12wHqQ6Q","flags":{},"type":0,"text":"Lost. Failure.","img":"icons/svg/d20-black.svg","resultId":"","weight":10,"range":[2,11],"drawn":false},{"_id":"LKAD09QSdaRg50s9","flags":{},"type":0,"text":"Failure, but spell is not lost.","img":"icons/svg/d20-black.svg","resultId":"","weight":2,"range":[12,13],"drawn":false},{"_id":"WHjQsUusaKfHhpBh","flags":{},"type":0,"text":"The caster can transform a small space to swamp for [[/roll 1d6]] turns. He must touch the space to be affected. The space is equal to eight cubic feet or roughly the size of a human-sized door or a 2' cube. Any mundane, non-living material can be affected (wood, stone, gold, dirt, etc.). The space changes into a semi-liquid muddy pool. <br /><br />If cast on a door, the door slides to the ground into a pool of gunk. If cast on a dungeon floor, the floor turns into a muddy pool a few inches deep. Living creatures are not affected, but their belongings (such as armor or a sword) can be. Magical items are not affected. At the end of the spell's duration, the space reforms to its original dimensions and nature.","img":"icons/svg/d20-black.svg","resultId":"","weight":2,"range":[14,15],"drawn":false},{"_id":"qWjZ5xEHeGr30cMs","flags":{},"type":0,"text":"The caster can transform a medium-sized space to swamp for [[/roll 1d6]] turns. He must touch the space to be affected. The caster can affect a space equal to 250 square feet or roughly the size of a large boulder 10' x 5' x 5'. Any mundane, non-living material can be affected (wood, stone, gold, dirt, etc.). The space changes into a semi-liquid muddy pool. If cast on a door, the door slides to the ground into a pool of gunk. <br /><br />If cast on a dungeon floor, the floor turns into a muddy pool a few inches deep. Living creatures are not transformed, but their belongings (such as armor or a sword) can be. Living creatures sitting or standing on the affected area sink into the mud as if they had been dropped into a swamp. If they are lightweight or can swim, there may be no impact, but heavily armored creatures may sink below the surface and drown. Magical items are not affected. At the end of the spell's duration, the space reforms to its original dimensions and nature.","img":"icons/svg/d20-black.svg","resultId":"","weight":4,"range":[16,19],"drawn":false},{"_id":"YQQvPbv0GCmLAz2x","flags":{},"type":0,"text":"The caster can transform a medium-sized space to swamp for [[/roll 1d6]] hours. He must touch the space to be affected. The caster can affect a space equal to 250 square feet or roughly the size of a large boulder 10' x 5' x 5'. Any mundane, non-living material can be affected (wood, stone, gold, dirt, etc.). The space changes into a semi-liquid muddy pool. If cast on a door, the door slides to the ground into a pool of gunk. <br /><br />If cast on a dungeon floor, the floor turns into a muddy pool a few inches deep. Living creatures are not transformed, but their belongings (such as armor or a sword) can be. Living creatures that were sitting or standing on the affected area sink into the mud as if they had been dropped into a swamp. If they are lightweight or can swim, there may be no impact, but heavily armored creatures may sink below the surface and drown. Magical items are not affected. At the end of the spell's duration, the space reforms to its original dimensions and nature.","img":"icons/svg/d20-black.svg","resultId":"","weight":2,"range":[20,21],"drawn":false},{"_id":"UoiUxqyp2cxQ7Hoj","flags":{},"type":0,"text":"The caster can transform a large field into swamp for [[/roll 1d6]] days. The caster touches the point of origin, then guides the dimensions of the space to be affected. He must have line of sight to the edges of the space. The caster can define a space up to 100' wide on each side, which is transformed into a swampy pool of mud, muck, and shallow water up to a few feet deep at various points. <br /><br />The field becomes difficult terrain. Lightly armored creatures move at half speed, but heavily armored warriors, as well as heavy creatures such as cows, horses, or minotaurs, become mired and unable to move. Some creatures may actually drown in the shallow water if they cannot be freed. Houses, battlements, and other fixed structures may sink several inches or more into the swamp. Magical items are not affected. At the end of the spell's duration, the space reforms to its original consistency and nature, although objects that have sunk may now be partially underground.","img":"icons/svg/d20-black.svg","resultId":"","weight":4,"range":[22,25],"drawn":false},{"_id":"LbhnB0XvjzZwyIDZ","flags":{},"type":0,"text":"The caster may choose among two results:The caster can transform a large field into swamp permanently. The caster touches the point of origin, then guides the dimensions of the space to be affected. He must have line of sight to the edges of the space. The caster can define a space up to 100' wide on each side, which is transformed into a swampy pool of mud, muck, and shallow water up to a few feet deep at various points. The field becomes difficult terrain. <br /><br />Lightly armored creatures move at half speed, but heavily armored warriors, as well as heavy creatures such as cows, horses, or minotaurs, become mired and unable to move. Some creatures may actually drown in the shallow water if they cannot be freed. Houses, battlements, and other fixed structures may sink several inches or more into the swamp. Magical items are not affected. At the end of the spell's duration, the space reforms to its original consistency and nature, although objects that have sunk may now be partially underground. <br /><br />Alternately, the caster can affect a large solid mass up to the size of a large house, permanently. Only mundane, non-living materials are affected (wood, stone, gold, dirt, etc.). The solid mass liquefies into a pile of mud and goo.","img":"icons/svg/d20-black.svg","resultId":"","weight":4,"range":[26,29],"drawn":false},{"_id":"hjTvJogB7NTyGtFf","flags":{},"type":0,"text":"The caster can permanently transform a vast expanse to swampy muck. The space is equal to up to 20,000 cubic feet or a field 200' x 100' to a depth of about a foot. This is also sufficient to affect a solid mass of almost 60' x 60' x 60' or a large castle. The caster can also use the ability to create a pit of mud; i.e., a space 10' wide at the very top and very deep. Heavy objects sink into the mud, armored humanoids may drown within it, and castles or houses can sink and be destroyed as their foundations shift. Magical items are not affected.","img":"icons/svg/d20-black.svg","resultId":"","weight":2,"range":[30,31],"drawn":false},{"_id":"furE9xGmKr0hcDCG","flags":{},"type":0,"text":"The caster can permanently transform a vast expanse to swampy muck or transform a single magic object permanently.If the caster transforms a vast expanse, the space is equal to up to 20,000 cubic feet or a field 200' x 100' to a depth of about a foot. This is also sufficient to affect a solid mass of almost 60' x 60' x 60' or a large castle. The caster can also use the ability to create a pit of mud; i.e., a space 10' wide at the very top and very deep. <br /><br />Heavy objects sink into the mud, armored humanoids may drown within it, and castles or houses can sink and be destroyed as their foundations shift.If the caster targets a magical item, he can target a single item up to human-sized (i.e., a sword, shield, staff, suit of armor, etc.), and that counts as the entire use of the spell. Magical objects receive a Fort saving throw to resist the effect. Otherwise, they are transformed to mud.","img":"icons/svg/d20-black.svg","resultId":"","weight":2,"range":[32,33],"drawn":false},{"_id":"YvMcvFYhblIlG3SV","flags":{},"type":0,"text":"The caster can permanently transform a vast expanse to swampy muck or transform a single magic object permanently or transform a single living creature to mud.If the caster transforms a vast expanse, the space is equal to up to 20,000 cubic feet or a field 200' x 100' to a depth of about a foot. This is also sufficient to affect a solid mass of almost 60' x 60' x 60', or a large castle. The caster can also use the ability to create a pit of mud; i.e., a space 10' wide at the very top and very deep. <br /><br />Heavy objects sink into the mud, armored humanoids may drown within it, and castles or houses can sink and be destroyed as their foundations shift.If the caster targets a magical item, he can target a single item up to human-sized (i.e., a sword, shield, staff, suit of armor, etc.) and that counts as the entire use of the spell. Magical objects receive a Fort saving throw to resist the effect. Otherwise, they are transformed to mud.If the caster targets a living creature, it must be touched to be affected. The living creature counts as the entire focus of the spell. Living creatures receive a Fort saving throw to resist the effect. Success indicates they are unaffected. Failure indicates they are transformed to mud and instantly slain.","img":"icons/svg/d20-black.svg","resultId":"","weight":66,"range":[34,99],"drawn":false}],"formula":"1d20","replacement":true,"displayRoll":true}
{"_id":"AkjVzB3aAFtp5fg0","name":"Tadpole Transformation","permission":{"default":0,"U5X07uKi3FMVWkQ1":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.dcc-compendium.spell-tables.tThptCnm4mi33FWL"}},"img":"modules/dcc-core-book/assets/svg/game-icons-net/tadpole.svg","description":"<h1>Tadpole Transformation</h1><p><strong>Level:</strong> 1</p><p><strong>Range:</strong> Self</p><p><strong>Duration:</strong> Varies</p><p><strong>Casting Time:</strong> 1 round</p><p><strong>Save:</strong> None</p><p><strong>Page:</strong> 325</p><br><p>A true servant of Bobugbubilz enjoys the calm of the deep swamp. The relaxing buzz of mosquitoes and biting flies, the cooling touch of muddy water, the irregular splashes of frogs and fishes, and the deep-throated calls of the swampland bullfrogs: these are the sounds and sights that bring happiness to Bobugbubilz and his thralls. This spell enables the caster to enjoy such sensations by changing his body to best accommodate them.</p><br><p><strong>Spell Data:</strong> @Compendium[dcc-core-book.dcc-core-spell-journals.Tadpole Transformation]{Tadpole Transformation}</p>","results":[{"_id":"cMZb3XLonAOkvS0u","flags":{},"type":0,"text":"Lost, failure, and patron taint.","img":"icons/svg/d20-black.svg","resultId":"","weight":1,"range":[-99,1],"drawn":false},{"_id":"ZOW3ZRxUMsRcgWko","flags":{},"type":0,"text":"Lost. Failure.","img":"icons/svg/d20-black.svg","resultId":"","weight":10,"range":[2,11],"drawn":false},{"_id":"RK43fgv2Yua0ScdX","flags":{},"type":0,"text":"The caster's legs double in girth, his ankle joints extend, and his legs double-back like a frog's. He can now hop distances equal to twice his normal walking speed. This means the caster can make a standing leap clear across chasms and pits or hop rapidly to move at twice his normal speed. The transformation lasts for [[/roll 1d6]] turns.","img":"icons/svg/d20-black.svg","resultId":"","weight":2,"range":[12,13],"drawn":false},{"_id":"WqsGpOflMxnpBvXz","flags":{},"type":0,"text":"The caster grows a stiff, tadpole-like tail. He can now swim at a speed equal to double his normal walking speed. The transformation lasts for [[/roll 1d6]] turns.","img":"icons/svg/d20-black.svg","resultId":"","weight":4,"range":[14,17],"drawn":false},{"_id":"oZfGmkHXwQdX2cBR","flags":{},"type":0,"text":"The caster grows gills in the side of his neck. He can now breathe underwater for [[/roll 1d6]] turns.","img":"icons/svg/d20-black.svg","resultId":"","weight":2,"range":[18,19],"drawn":false},{"_id":"z6J6HyiV1LZuRPPW","flags":{},"type":0,"text":"The caster's mouth distorts into the wide, gulping maw of a frog, and his tongue lengthens. He gains a bite attack that deals [[/roll 1d6]] damage plus Strength modifier. Additionally, the caster can extend his sticky tongue with great accuracy. <br /><br />As a ranged attack, he can target any object within 40' with his tongue. Success indicates the caster latches onto the object and can reel it back with an effective Strength of 20 (for purposes of the sticky tongue only)—the target must make an opposed Strength check to resist. The effect lasts for [[/roll 1d6]] turns.","img":"icons/svg/d20-black.svg","resultId":"","weight":4,"range":[20,23],"drawn":false},{"_id":"pfsUya08h51dZVhf","flags":{},"type":0,"text":"The caster undergoes a broad transformation that grants him frog legs, a stiff tadpole tail, gills, and a frog mouth, as the above four results. The effect lasts for [[/roll 1d6]] turns.","img":"icons/svg/d20-black.svg","resultId":"","weight":4,"range":[24,27],"drawn":false},{"_id":"wsXacjglTG4iZGBb","flags":{},"type":0,"text":"The caster gains all effects from results 24-27 above, and the duration is extended to [[/roll 1d6]] hours.","img":"icons/svg/d20-black.svg","resultId":"","weight":2,"range":[28,29],"drawn":false},{"_id":"IUVt3rJNKfrjkFgQ","flags":{},"type":0,"text":"The caster is transformed into a walking avatar of Bobugbubilz. His girth and mass grows to roughly double normal. His arms and legs thicken, he grows a tadpole-like tail, and his frog-like mouth is imposing in size. He gains the hopping, swimming, breathing, biting, and tongue-lashing abilities outlined in results 12-23 for a period of [[/roll 1d6]] hours. In addition, due to his larger size and constitution, he gains [[/roll 2d6]] temporary hit points and is treated as having a Strength of 18 for all normal purposes (including melee combat).","img":"icons/svg/d20-black.svg","resultId":"","weight":2,"range":[30,31],"drawn":false},{"_id":"TCBTzalZm9Xh7MoD","flags":{},"type":0,"text":"The caster is transformed into a walking avatar of Bobugbubilz. His girth and mass grows to roughly triple normal. His arms and legs thicken, he grows a tadpole-like tail, and his frog-like mouth is imposing in size. He gains the hopping, swimming, breathing, biting, and tongue-lashing abilities outlined in results 12-23 for a period of [[/roll 1d6]] days, which can be cut short at any point he wishes. In addition, due to his larger size and constitution, he gains [[/roll 3d6]] temporary hit points and is treated as having a Strength of 22 for all normal purposes (including melee combat).","img":"icons/svg/d20-black.svg","resultId":"","weight":68,"range":[32,99],"drawn":false}],"formula":"1d20","replacement":true,"displayRoll":true}
{"_id":"DPqfBYV5xs96bWPG","name":"Phylactery of the Soul","permission":{"default":0,"U5X07uKi3FMVWkQ1":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.dcc-compendium.spell-tables.sAjsQNybIdRBx5eJ"}},"img":"modules/dcc-core-book/assets/svg/game-icons-net/health-potion.svg","description":"<h1>Phylactery of the Soul</h1><p><strong>Level:</strong> 3</p><p><strong>Range:</strong> Self</p><p><strong>Duration:</strong> Variable</p><p><strong>Casting Time:</strong> 1 day</p><p><strong>Save:</strong> See below</p><p><strong>Page:</strong> 341</p><br><p>Following in the Old Master&rsquo;s path, the caster has succeeded in learning how to place his soul within an amulet or gem (worth no less than [[/roll 1d8]] x 100 gp) while still maintaining control of his mortal body.</p>\n<p>The caster has no awareness of the phylactery or its surroundings when inhabiting a body. If his mortal form is slain, his awareness returns to the phylactery and he has a variable period of time to inhabit a new body before his soul departs. Any new body must be living and physically touch the phylactery; the victim receives a Will save vs. spell check to resist being forced from its shell.</p><br><p><strong>Spell Data:</strong> @Compendium[dcc-core-book.dcc-core-spell-journals.Phylactery of the Soul]{Phylactery of the Soul}</p>","results":[{"_id":"cdTbDgBBMrHDPnfe","flags":{},"type":0,"text":"Lost, failure, and patron taint.","img":"icons/svg/d20-black.svg","resultId":"","weight":1,"range":[-99,1],"drawn":false},{"_id":"X970es0RnhXK96YQ","flags":{},"type":0,"text":"Lost. Failure.","img":"icons/svg/d20-black.svg","resultId":"","weight":10,"range":[2,11],"drawn":false},{"_id":"a9wa7qhevXDlobYT","flags":{},"type":0,"text":"Failure, but spell is not lost.","img":"icons/svg/d20-black.svg","resultId":"","weight":4,"range":[12,15],"drawn":false},{"_id":"xxX8ynQdtRV6ghp3","flags":{},"type":0,"text":"The caster places his soul within the chosen phylactery. His body can travel no further than 10 miles from the phylactery; any further distance causes the body to die and the soul's awareness to return to its vessel. Without a body to sustain him, the caster has [[/roll 1d6]]+CL hours to inhabit a new body before his soul dissipates into nothingness.","img":"icons/svg/d20-black.svg","resultId":"","weight":2,"range":[16,17],"drawn":false},{"_id":"8kFqxg6ukTZix2IK","flags":{},"type":0,"text":"The caster places his soul within the chosen phylactery. His body can travel no further than 50 miles from the phylactery; any further distance causes the body to die and the soul's awareness to return to its vessel. Without a body to sustain him, the caster has [[/roll 1d10]]+CL days to inhabit a new body before his soul dissipates into nothingness.","img":"icons/svg/d20-black.svg","resultId":"","weight":4,"range":[18,21],"drawn":false},{"_id":"9GwcaY2RNDAz58d4","flags":{},"type":0,"text":"The caster places his soul within the chosen phylactery. His body can travel no further than 100 miles from the phylactery; any further distance causes the body to die and the soul's awareness to return to its vessel. Without a body to sustain him, the caster has [[/roll 1d16]]+CL days to inhabit a new body before his soul dissipates into nothingness.","img":"icons/svg/d20-black.svg","resultId":"","weight":2,"range":[22,23],"drawn":false},{"_id":"HO1zGw3tf4YOA3Kk","flags":{},"type":0,"text":"The caster places his soul within the chosen phylactery. His body can travel no further than 500 miles from the phylactery; any further distance causes the body to die and the soul's awareness to return to its vessel. Without a body to sustain him, the caster has [[/roll 1d20]]+CL days to inhabit a new body before his soul dissipates into nothingness.","img":"icons/svg/d20-black.svg","resultId":"","weight":3,"range":[24,26],"drawn":false},{"_id":"TlkLeHbDsyU1nC6D","flags":{},"type":0,"text":"The caster places his soul within the chosen phylactery. His body can travel no further than 1,000 miles from the phylactery; any further distance causes the body to die and the soul's awareness to return to its vessel. Without a body to sustain him, the caster has [[/roll 1d6]]+CL weeks to inhabit a new body before his soul dissipates into nothingness.","img":"icons/svg/d20-black.svg","resultId":"","weight":5,"range":[27,31],"drawn":false},{"_id":"O5VEKUvQE1zT0pag","flags":{},"type":0,"text":"The caster places his soul within the chosen phylactery. His body can travel anywhere on this plane, but extraplanar travel (even for an instant) causes his body to die and the soul's awareness to return to its vessel. Without a body to sustain him, the caster has [[/roll 1d10]]+CL weeks to inhabit a new body before his soul dissipates into nothingness.","img":"icons/svg/d20-black.svg","resultId":"","weight":2,"range":[32,33],"drawn":false},{"_id":"e7pcgyn2dyWc9vwu","flags":{},"type":0,"text":"The caster places his soul within the chosen phylactery. His body can travel anywhere in the multiverse without restrictions. If the caster's body is slain, he has [[/roll 1d16]] + CL weeks to inhabit a new body before his soul dissipates into nothingness.","img":"icons/svg/d20-black.svg","resultId":"","weight":2,"range":[34,35],"drawn":false},{"_id":"MmaMcjgp2Dpym5zH","flags":{},"type":0,"text":"The caster places his soul within the chosen phylactery. His body can travel anywhere in the multiverse without danger. If the caster's body is slain, he has [[/roll 1d100]] + CL years to inhabit a new body before his soul dissipates into nothingness.","img":"icons/svg/d20-black.svg","resultId":"","weight":64,"range":[36,99],"drawn":false}],"formula":"1d20","replacement":true,"displayRoll":true}
{"_id":"Jvhur3f9deyIdb6x","name":"Invoke Ithha, Prince of Elemental Wind","permission":{"default":0,"wWErSsSXezizF0nw":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"RollTable.mj40c3DHmOJGniRQ"}},"img":"modules/dcc-core-book/assets/svg/game-icons-net/wind-slap.svg","description":"<h1>Invoke Ithha, Prince of Elemental Wind</h1><p><strong>Level:</strong> 1</p><p><strong>Range:</strong> Self</p><p><strong>Duration:</strong> Varies</p><p><strong>Casting Time:</strong> 1 round, and the spell may be cast only a limited number of times, according to results of patron bond.</p><p><strong>Save:</strong> None</p><p><strong>Page:</strong> 356</p><br><p>Ithha, prince of elemental wind, serves as one example of the elemental pacts that can be made. Ithha is a demi- god who seeks to subjugate the earth elemental Grom and his minions. Ithha grants limited control over wind and the ability to summon air elementals</p><br><p><strong>Spell Data:</strong> @Compendium[dcc-core-book.dcc-core-spell-journals.Invoke Ithha, Prince of Elemental Wind]{Invoke Ithha, Prince of Elemental Wind}</p>","results":[{"_id":"Qn1WRMZ8lyJduaTp","flags":{},"type":0,"text":"Lost, failure, and worse! Roll [[/roll 1d6]] modified by Luck: (3 or less) corruption + patron taint; (4-5) corruption; (6+) patron taint.","img":"icons/svg/d20-black.svg","resultId":"","weight":1,"range":[-99,1],"drawn":false},{"_id":"8h3LpsdfcKS0qXgj","flags":{},"type":0,"text":"Failure. Unlike other spells, invoke patron may not be lost for the day. Depending on the results of patron bond, the wizard may still be able to cast it.","img":"icons/svg/d20-black.svg","resultId":"","weight":10,"range":[2,11],"drawn":false},{"_id":"kcUG5Eqj2nVO0mfd","flags":{},"type":0,"text":"Earth-enemy. For the next turn, the caster and all allies within 10’ gain a +2 bonus to attacks, damage, and spell checks against creatures of earth or stone.","img":"icons/svg/d20-black.svg","resultId":"","weight":2,"range":[12,13],"drawn":false},{"_id":"FjMm2dXqXgiB4lc1","flags":{},"type":0,"text":"Protective vortex. The caster is surrounded by a whirling vortex that flings aside all incoming missiles, and melee attackers must struggle to lift their blades against the wind. For the next turn, all missile fire attacks that “hit” the caster have an automatic 50% chance of missing, and the caster receives a +2 bonus to AC.","img":"icons/svg/d20-black.svg","resultId":"","weight":4,"range":[14,17],"drawn":false},{"_id":"KeCRAj5zurXGNhod","flags":{},"type":0,"text":"Sandstorm. A swirling, turbulent cone of air emanates from the caster’s fingertip, pulling up sand and grit from the ground to produce a veritable sandstorm. The caster can target one enemy within 50’, who takes [[/roll 1d12]] damage from abrasion. <br /><br />The sandstorm continues to whirl around that same target, following him if he moves and inflicting [[/roll 1d10]] damage on the next round, then [[/roll 1d8]], [[/roll 1d6]], and finally [[/roll 1d4]] on the fifth and final round. Each round, the target can make a DC 20 Fort save to avoid damage.","img":"icons/svg/d20-black.svg","resultId":"","weight":2,"range":[18,19],"drawn":false},{"_id":"7NBpr1zCmWFeeWxE","flags":{},"type":0,"text":"Suffocation. The caster targets one air-breathing enemy within 100’ and points to him. All the air in the target’s lungs is sucked out. The target begins suffocating, taking [[/roll 1d6]] Stamina damage immediately unless he succeeds on a DC 20 Fort save. <br /><br />If the save is failed, the target takes another [[/roll 1d6]] Stamina damage on the following round with another save to resist. Each time the target fails a save, the suffocation continues another round, lasting until he succeeds on a save or until he reaches 0 Stamina, at which point he dies.","img":"icons/svg/d20-black.svg","resultId":"","weight":4,"range":[20,23],"drawn":false},{"_id":"6nWCbXvsW3OyyPwV","flags":{},"type":0,"text":"Elemental transformation. The caster and all his equipment transform into gaseous form. He can fly at twice his normal speed and is immune to physical attack from mundane weapons, though he can be harmed by spells and magical attacks. The transformation lasts for 1 hour or until he wills it to end. While in gaseous form, the caster cannot attack physically but can cast spells that do not have limitations associated with his new form.","img":"icons/svg/d20-black.svg","resultId":"","weight":4,"range":[24,27],"drawn":false},{"_id":"WrKkfdbW7bUr6v5B","flags":{},"type":0,"text":"Summon invisible companion. The invisible companion performs the caster’s bidding for 1 day. It can fly at a speed of 100’ and can perform any task as a normal man, though it is invisible. It can attack enemies at +6 for [[/roll 2d6]] damage. If attacked, it has AC 16 and 60 hit points, although attackers can only fight it in melee (unless they cleverly reveal it somehow), and even then automatically miss 75% of the time.","img":"icons/svg/d20-black.svg","resultId":"","weight":2,"range":[28,29],"drawn":false},{"_id":"H0AM1ls2lqjPlvc4","flags":{},"type":0,"text":"Summon elemental. The caster calls forth a gust of sentient wind. It appears immediately and obeys commands for [[/roll 2d6]] rounds, then departs. It has the stats and abilities of an 8 HD air elemental (see page 411).","img":"icons/svg/d20-black.svg","resultId":"","weight":2,"range":[30,31],"drawn":false},{"_id":"w4D64pTsFugA7m1D","flags":{},"type":0,"text":"Summon multiple elementals. The caster calls forth two gusts of sentient wind. They appear immediately and obey commands for [[/roll 2d6]] rounds, then depart. They have the stats and abilities of 12 HD air elementals (see page 411)","img":"icons/svg/d20-black.svg","resultId":"","weight":1,"range":[32,99],"drawn":false}],"formula":"1d20","replacement":true,"displayRoll":true}
{"_id":"LsDM7dzsWULrtuqa","name":"Forest Walk","permission":{"default":0,"U5X07uKi3FMVWkQ1":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.dcc-compendium.spell-tables.zPdqmBIQbWbG1kb9"}},"img":"modules/dcc-core-book/assets/svg/game-icons-net/forest.svg","description":"<h1>Forest Walk</h1><p><strong>Level:</strong> 1</p><p><strong>Range:</strong> Varies</p><p><strong>Duration:</strong> Varies</p><p><strong>Casting Time:</strong> 1 action</p><p><strong>Save:</strong> None</p><p><strong>Page:</strong> 345</p><br><p>Conversant with the spirits and powers of Elfland, the caster employs the hidden byways and secret wynds of the fairy realm, teleporting from one tree to another. The caster must travel between trees of the same species, generally limiting his travel to similar biomes. For example, a caster cannot travel from</p>\n<p>a rain forest to a deciduous forest or from a northern conifer stand to aa temperate broadleaf woodland.</p>\n<p>At the judge&rsquo;s discretion, appearing from within a tree typically confers surprise. The caster can specify a specific tree to emerge from of which he has knowledge, but he does not need knowledge of the place to which he travels: he can state, for example, &ldquo;I wish to emerge from an oak tree in the orc realms 100 miles north of here.&rdquo;</p><br><p><strong>Spell Data:</strong> @Compendium[dcc-core-book.dcc-core-spell-journals.Forest Walk]{Forest Walk}</p>","results":[{"_id":"8Dsbl39DVC6qT1TT","flags":{},"type":0,"text":"Lost, failure, and patron taint.","img":"icons/svg/d20-black.svg","resultId":"","weight":1,"range":[-99,1],"drawn":false},{"_id":"hjfmx8GvvmqLnxhy","flags":{},"type":0,"text":"Lost. Failure.","img":"icons/svg/d20-black.svg","resultId":"","weight":10,"range":[2,11],"drawn":false},{"_id":"ai2noBRyBIlUQ4Xx","flags":{},"type":0,"text":"The caster steps through one tree and instantly emerges from another tree up 100 yards away.","img":"icons/svg/d20-black.svg","resultId":"","weight":2,"range":[12,13],"drawn":false},{"_id":"S3ABhDXh1zBfgtCH","flags":{},"type":0,"text":"The caster steps through one tree and instantly emerges from another tree within the same forest, up to one mile distant.","img":"icons/svg/d20-black.svg","resultId":"","weight":4,"range":[14,17],"drawn":false},{"_id":"ZV4fvHlx8NRWiKMp","flags":{},"type":0,"text":"The caster steps through one tree and instantly emerges from another tree within the same forest, up to 100 miles distant.","img":"icons/svg/d20-black.svg","resultId":"","weight":2,"range":[18,19],"drawn":false},{"_id":"5yVFNUeIBJTQRPTY","flags":{},"type":0,"text":"The caster and up to [[/roll 1d4]] + CL allies step through a tree and are instantly transported to another tree within the same forest, up to 100 miles distant.","img":"icons/svg/d20-black.svg","resultId":"","weight":4,"range":[20,23],"drawn":false},{"_id":"JCl4PD7QJy5AGLPf","flags":{},"type":0,"text":"The caster and up to [[/roll 1d8]] + CL allies step through a tree and are instantly transported to another tree within the same forest, up to 100 miles distant.","img":"icons/svg/d20-black.svg","resultId":"","weight":4,"range":[24,27],"drawn":false},{"_id":"YYOvHLkCdShnVQS4","flags":{},"type":0,"text":"The caster and up to [[/roll 1d12]] + CL allies step through a tree and are instantly transported to another tree within the same forest, up to 1,000 miles distant.","img":"icons/svg/d20-black.svg","resultId":"","weight":2,"range":[28,29],"drawn":false},{"_id":"hnKAXqCqNgPu0m6F","flags":{},"type":0,"text":"The caster and up to CL x 100 allies step through a tree and are instantly transported to another tree, anywhere on the same plane. This spell remains active long enough for all allies to step through the tree. This spell can be used to allow an army to march through a tree and arrive at a distance place. Allies can be mounted on horses or even in boats provided the tree is adjacent to a waterway.","img":"icons/svg/d20-black.svg","resultId":"","weight":2,"range":[30,31],"drawn":false},{"_id":"oj5UAzGEnV4NoVm5","flags":{},"type":0,"text":"The caster and any number of allies can step through a tree to be instantly transported to another tree, on any plane. Of course, trees of the same species typically grow on similar planes of existence, so planar travel with this is limited, but a carefully cultivated specimen nurtured in advance of casting of this spell can be used as an \"anchor point\" on another plane. Servants of the King of Elfland use this spell to instantly travel between waystations on his realm of existence and many other planes.","img":"icons/svg/d20-black.svg","resultId":"","weight":68,"range":[32,99],"drawn":false}],"formula":"1d20","replacement":true,"displayRoll":true}
{"_id":"NaWlcMLXHezbIDo6","name":"Invoke Yddgrrl, the World Root","permission":{"default":0,"U5X07uKi3FMVWkQ1":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"RollTable.aL1uwPYWvihRaWRk"}},"img":"modules/dcc-core-book/assets/svg/game-icons-net/floating-platforms.svg","description":"<h1>Invoke Yddgrrl, the World Root</h1><p><strong>Level:</strong> 1</p><p><strong>Range:</strong> Self</p><p><strong>Duration:</strong> Varies</p><p><strong>Casting Time:</strong> 1 round, and the spell may be cast only a limited number of times, according to results of patron bond.</p><p><strong>Save:</strong> None</p><p><strong>Page:</strong> 354</p><br><p>Yddgrrl is the root from which all living plants grow. He is the guardian of the forest, worshipped by treants, sentient plants, and some druids. Yddgrrl&rsquo;s presence can be felt in the quiet dew-times and the deep calm of the green, when the meditating plant-life feels his nourishment. He controls the soil, the air, and the rain of the forest, and appears as a fast-growing root that breaks the surface of the forest floor to bring aid where needed. Yddgrrl asks little of his followers save that they meditate on the serenity of the green and defend the forests against all enemies, especially its greatest foes: fire and the axe. Yddgrrl dwells in a unique plane of existence at the intersection of the elemental planes of air, water, and earth, where he forever battles the forces of elemental fire.</p><br><p><strong>Spell Data:</strong> @Compendium[dcc-core-book.dcc-core-spell-journals.Invoke Yddgrrl, the World Root]{Invoke Yddgrrl, the World Root}</p>","results":[{"_id":"ALXj8LneDB0pXRzI","flags":{},"type":0,"text":"Lost, failure, and worse! Roll [[/roll 1d6]] modified by Luck: (3 or less) corruption + patron taint; (4-5) corruption; (6+) patron taint.","img":"icons/svg/d20-black.svg","resultId":"","weight":1,"range":[-99,1],"drawn":false},{"_id":"SUrOUu22zztNxyJB","flags":{},"type":0,"text":"Failure. Unlike other spells, invoke patron may not be lost for the day. Depending on the results of patron bond, the wizard may still be able to cast it.","img":"icons/svg/d20-black.svg","resultId":"","weight":10,"range":[2,11],"drawn":false},{"_id":"O2mcD7xU1xyKwx7s","flags":{},"type":0,"text":"Yddgrrl protects the caster from the forest’s enemies. Roots grow about his body and limbs with no negative impact to mobility. For [[/roll 1d6]]+CL rounds, the roots protect the caster, who takes half damage from fire and bladed weapons.","img":"icons/svg/d20-black.svg","resultId":"","weight":2,"range":[12,13],"drawn":false},{"_id":"D79kNeVpSswCaysi","flags":{},"type":0,"text":"Yddgrrl sends a torrential rain to protect the caster. A cloud materializes above the caster’s head (even if underground) and the rainstorm erupts. The rain is centered on the caster and extends [[/roll 1d4]] x 10’ from him in all directions. All natural fires are automatically extinguished. <br /><br />Magical fires are also extinguished unless they make a Will save against the spell check result (using the original caster’s Will modifier). Fire-based magic used while the rainstorm is ongoing (e.g., fireball) is severely hampered and does only half damage. Visibility is restricted, inflicting a -2 attack penalty to all missile fire attacks. The rain storm continues for [[/roll 1d6]]+CL rounds.","img":"icons/svg/d20-black.svg","resultId":"","weight":4,"range":[14,17],"drawn":false},{"_id":"Jqp3d1McdKmdR8WP","flags":{},"type":0,"text":"Yddgrrl strengthens the caster’s skin to better resist the blade of the axe. The caster’s skin thickens to resemble bark, and he gains a +4 AC bonus. The effect lasts for [[/roll 1d4]] turns.","img":"icons/svg/d20-black.svg","resultId":"","weight":2,"range":[18,19],"drawn":false},{"_id":"LGuNCrpAUZo6fy3C","flags":{},"type":0,"text":"Yddgrrl provides nourishment. The caster’s legs sprout thin roots that seek out the ground. If the caster is standing on dirt or stone, he heals [[/roll 1d8]] hit points at the end of each round in which he does not move. This continues until he moves or returns to maximum hit points.","img":"icons/svg/d20-black.svg","resultId":"","weight":4,"range":[20,23],"drawn":false},{"_id":"nysPBOEl1S2cO8Ai","flags":{},"type":0,"text":"Yddgrrl sends the world-root to aid his follower. The tip of an enormous tree root bursts forth from the ground, swaying like a snake, and proceeds to attack a target of the caster’s designation. It attacks with a +8 slam for [[/roll 1d6+6]] points of damage on the caster’s initiative count. It can target any creature within 40’ of the caster. <br /><br />The world-root remains for [[/roll 1d6]]+CL rounds, and cannot be slain during this time; even if severed or killed, another root simply sprouts beside it. The caster does not need to concentrate in order to continue directing its actions.","img":"icons/svg/d20-black.svg","resultId":"","weight":4,"range":[24,27],"drawn":false},{"_id":"RrIDzBMLlhIPzB6X","flags":{},"type":0,"text":"A complex tangle of tree roots bursts from the earth to entangle an enemy of the caster’s choosing. The enemy must be within 100’. He receives a Reflex save against the spell check DC to jump free; otherwise, he is trapped in place by the roots. The roots are permanent; the target can be freed only by chopping him free (must do 40 points of damage to the AC 12 roots).","img":"icons/svg/d20-black.svg","resultId":"","weight":2,"range":[28,29],"drawn":false},{"_id":"fNpQC1GAFSjHvuXC","flags":{},"type":0,"text":"A colossal tree-man bursts from the ground nearby and fights on behalf of the caster. He moves on the caster’s initiative and the caster can perform other actions while directing him. The tree-man remains for [[/roll 1d4]]+CL rounds. Tree-man: Atk slam +12 melee (dmg [[/roll 2d6+6]]); AC 17; HD [[/roll 6d8]]; MV 20’; Act [[/roll 2d20]]; SP takes 2x damage from fire; SV Fort +8, Ref +1, Will +8; AL N.","img":"icons/svg/d20-black.svg","resultId":"","weight":2,"range":[30,31],"drawn":false},{"_id":"rCdlMokze2ssPuEO","flags":{},"type":0,"text":"Yddgrrl sends two tree-men to fight for the caster, as result 30-31 above.","img":"icons/svg/d20-black.svg","resultId":"","weight":469,"range":[32,99],"drawn":false}],"formula":"1d20","replacement":true,"displayRoll":true}
{"_id":"QKaDIvj4oFXhe8us","name":"Kith of the Hydra","permission":{"default":0,"U5X07uKi3FMVWkQ1":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.dcc-compendium.spell-tables.Zk3vr61BQn9no6wj"}},"img":"modules/dcc-core-book/assets/svg/game-icons-net/hydra.svg","description":"<h1>Kith of the Hydra</h1><p><strong>Level:</strong> 2</p><p><strong>Range:</strong> Self</p><p><strong>Duration:</strong> Varies</p><p><strong>Casting Time:</strong> 1 hour</p><p><strong>Save:</strong> None</p><p><strong>Page:</strong> 334</p><br><p>Azi Dahaka is the sire and patron of all hydras. By embracing the secret of the hydra, the caster shirks death&rsquo;s coil, gaining the ability to return from the dead&mdash;but only at great sacrifice. Wounds knit, shattered bones mend, and even limbs grow back. However, ongoing damage (for instance, if the caster&rsquo;s body remains crushed beneath a boulder) does not cease. If the body is utterly and entirely destroyed, the spell fails. If a caster attempts to recast the spell while still under the influence of a previous casting, he is irrevocably transformed into a mindless hydra. This spell requires a minimum spellburn of 4 points.</p><br><p><strong>Spell Data:</strong> @Compendium[dcc-core-book.dcc-core-spell-journals.Kith of the Hydra]{Kith of the Hydra}</p>","results":[{"_id":"JhaAZu9WT8BhevLC","flags":{},"type":0,"text":"Lost, failure, and patron taint.","img":"icons/svg/d20-black.svg","resultId":"","weight":1,"range":[-99,1],"drawn":false},{"_id":"7hWfuf26Il2QGSW1","flags":{},"type":0,"text":"Lost. Failure.","img":"icons/svg/d20-black.svg","resultId":"","weight":10,"range":[2,11],"drawn":false},{"_id":"py1edyrdhK5pPzS1","flags":{},"type":0,"text":"Failure, but spell is not lost.","img":"icons/svg/d20-black.svg","resultId":"","weight":2,"range":[12,13],"drawn":false},{"_id":"AdV5cIi2DpzPk7ll","flags":{},"type":0,"text":"If the caster dies within the next hour, his body is restored to full hit points upon the next new moon. Roll [[/roll 1d3]] u