{"_id":"cGJMuI6JU7ZWpNL1","name":"Invoke Sezrekan","permission":{"default":0,"wWErSsSXezizF0nw":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"RollTable.deqNJCmPsmJxbrVn"}},"img":"modules/dcc-core-book/assets/svg/game-icons-net/wizard-staff.svg","description":"<h1>Invoke Sezrekan</h1><p><strong>Level:</strong> 1</p><p><strong>Range:</strong> Self</p><p><strong>Duration:</strong> Varies</p><p><strong>Casting Time:</strong> 1 round, and the spell may be cast only a limited number of times, according to results of patron bond.</p><p><strong>Save:</strong> None</p><p><strong>Page:</strong> 336</p><br><p>Regarded as the wickedest of wizards ever to plague the Known World, Sezrekan the Elder was born to a peasant family and cursed with the knowledge of higher worlds. Straining to hear the music of the heavenly spheres, the aspiring wizard&nbsp; found only chaos and madness. Forsaking patron and liege alike, Sezrekan sought to free himself of the world and his mortal coil, regardless of the cost. Those who claim him as their patron are expected to follow in the Master&rsquo;s&nbsp; footsteps, sacrificing kith and kin in the single-minded pursuit of mastery of self and thereby the multiverse. The Old Master has little regard for those that cannot help themselves, offering his aid only to spellcasters of proven dedication and talent.</p><br><p><strong>Spell Data:</strong> @Compendium[dcc-core-book.dcc-core-spell-journals.Invoke Sezrekan]{Invoke Sezrekan}</p>","results":[{"_id":"RPtm8XpPn58k21Xa","flags":{},"type":0,"text":"Lost, failure, and worse! Roll [[/roll 1d6]] modified by Luck: (3 or less) corruption + patron taint; (4-5) corruption; (6+) patron taint.","img":"icons/svg/d20-black.svg","resultId":"","weight":1,"range":[-99,1],"drawn":false},{"_id":"lfwfIu4ibEPzeuhn","flags":{},"type":0,"text":"Failure. Unlike other spells, invoke patron may not be lost for the day. Depending on the results of patron bond, the wizard may still be able to cast it.","img":"icons/svg/d20-black.svg","resu