{"_id":"fzblcOVWts4oYEEa","name":"War Horn of Elfland","permission":{"default":0,"U5X07uKi3FMVWkQ1":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.dcc-compendium.spell-tables.zXB8Fj7VBapF5m2Y"}},"img":"modules/dcc-core-book/assets/svg/game-icons-net/hunting-horn.svg","description":"<h1>War Horn of Elfland</h1><p><strong>Level:</strong> 2</p><p><strong>Range:</strong> Self</p><p><strong>Duration:</strong> Varies</p><p><strong>Casting Time:</strong> 1 round</p><p><strong>Save:</strong> None</p><p><strong>Page:</strong> 346</p><br><p>The caster sounds a great war horn, calling the armies of Elfland to his side. Faithful unto death and fierce in battle, their tie to the mortal plane is but short and fleeting. The spell requires sounding a horn carved from a beast of 5 HD or greater. If the horn is set with precious jewels and metals (worth no less than 500 gp), the caster receives a +2 bonus to his spell checks (though a natural 1 still results in a patron taint). The horn must be held and sounded once every three rounds the spell is in effect. Sounding the horn requires an action, and if the horn fails to be sounded, the spell comes to an end. The warriors&rsquo; bodies and kit vanish</p>\n<p>when slain or the spells ends. The stats for the various allies are as follows:</p>\n<p><strong>Trollish Spearmen:</strong> Init +0; Atk spear +1 melee (dmg [[/roll 1d8]]); AC 15; HD [[/roll 1d8]]; HP 1; MV 30&rsquo;; Act [[/roll 1d20]]; SV Fort +1, Ref +1, Will +0; AL C.</p>\n<p><strong>Brownie Slingers:</strong> Init +0; Atk sling +1 ranged (dmg [[/roll 1d4]]) or short sword +1 melee (dmg [[/roll 1d6-1]]); AC 14; HD [[/roll 1d6]]; HP 1; MV 30&rsquo;; Act [[/roll 1d20]]; SV Fort +0, Ref +1, Will -1; AL C.</p>\n<p><strong>Hob Footmen:</strong> Init +0; Atk longsword +2 melee (dmg [[/roll 1d8+2]]); AC 17; HD [[/roll 2d8]]; HP 1; MV 30&rsquo;; Act [[/roll 1d20]]; SV Fort +1, Ref +1, Will +1; AL C.</p>\n<p><strong>Pixie Archers:</strong> Init +0; Atk Tiny sword +2 melee (dmg [[/roll 1d4]] plus sleep) or pixie bow +2 (dmg [[/roll 1d4]] plus sleep); AC 16; HD [[/roll 2d6]]; HP 1; MV 40&rsquo; flight; Act [[/roll 1d20]]; SP pixie dust weapons (DC 15 Fort save on hit or sleep for [[/roll 1d6]] hours); SV Fort +1, Ref +2, Will +0; AL C.</p>\n<p><strong>Fomorians:</strong> Init +0; Atk Large morningstar +4 melee (dmg [[/roll 1d12+4]]) or hurling stone +2 ranged (dmg [[/roll 1d8+4]]); AC 16; HD [[/roll 5d10]]; HP 1; MV 45&rsquo;; Act [[/roll 2d20]]; SV Fort +4, Ref +1, Will +0; AL C.</p><br><p><strong>Spell Data:</strong> @Compendium[dcc-core-book.dcc-core-spell-journals.War Horn of Elfland]{War Horn of Elfland}</p>","results":[{"_id":"eCnvnYG1bWyw9s0H","flags":{},"type":0,"text":"Lost, failure, and patron taint.","img":"icons/svg/d20-black.svg","resultId":"","weight":1,"range":[-99,1],"drawn":false},{"_id":"WpAFCrvdzOxgNyGa","flags":{},"type":0,"text":"Lost. Failure.","img":"icons/svg/d20-black.svg","resultId":"","weight":10,"range":[2,11],"drawn":false},{"_id":"zeQA46NUg3a3EikC","flags":{},"type":0,"text":"Failure, but spell is not lost.","img":"icons/svg/d20-black.svg","resultId":"","weight":2,"range":[12,13],"drawn":false},{"_id":"8sHnJAvhdsyqqGcs","flags":{},"type":0,"text":"A group of [[/roll 1d5]] brownie slingers answer the call. Each is armed with a sling, a satchel of sling bullets, and a short sword, but vanishes after taking a single point of damage. The spell lasts for [[/roll 1d6]]+CL rounds, as long as the horn is sounded once every three rounds, or until all the fae are dismissed.","img":"icons/svg/d20-black.svg","resultId":"","weight":2,"range":[14,15],"drawn":false},{"_id":"CPkDqte3peuKtrNw","flags":{},"type":0,"text":"A body of [[/roll 1d5]]+CL trollish spearmen supported by [[/roll 1d5]] brownie slingers heed the call. The spearmen carry flashing long spears. Each ally vanishes after taking a single point of damage. The spell lasts for [[/roll 1d8]]+CL rounds, as long as the horn is sounded once every three rounds, or until all the fae