st of Elfland. The spell lasts for [[/roll 1d24]]+CL rounds. Immediately re-roll the spell check to determine the type and number of fae that answer the call, re-rolling any spell failures or results of 32+. As long as the caster continues to sound the horn, re-roll the spell check again every third round, as new allies answer the call.","img":"icons/svg/d20-black.svg","resultId":"","weight":2,"range":[32,33],"drawn":false},{"_id":"CrldxRScLqvPvVgT","flags":{},"type":0,"text":"The full host of Elfland comes to the caster's aid, stepping fully into the mortal realm. Immediately re-roll the spell check to determine the type and number of fae that answer the call, re-rolling any spell failures or results of 32+. As long as the caster continue to sound the horn, re-roll the spell check again every third round, as new allies answer the call. Each type of fae steps into the mortal realm with full hit points, not just 1 point, and are not dismissed until they reach 1 hit point. The spell ends when dismissed by the caster or by the King of Elfland himself.","img":"icons/svg/d20-black.svg","resultId":"","weight":66,"range":[34,99],"drawn":false}],"formula":"1d20","replacement":true,"displayRoll":true}
{"_id":"iqnJZCE263Wi6PW5","name":"Bottomfeeder Bond","permission":{"default":0,"U5X07uKi3FMVWkQ1":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.dcc-compendium.spell-tables.yEYmB21aG3crmMk5"}},"img":"modules/dcc-core-book/assets/svg/game-icons-net/frog.svg","description":"<h1>Bottomfeeder Bond</h1><p><strong>Level:</strong> 3</p><p><strong>Range:</strong> 30' or more</p><p><strong>Duration:</strong> 1 turn+</p><p><strong>Casting Time:</strong> 2 rounds</p><p><strong>Save:</strong> Will vs spell check DC for intelleigent</p><p><strong>Page:</strong> 328</p><br><p>Bobugbubilz holds court on a distant plane populated by endless horizons of swampland. In this place he is lord of all amphibians, as well as many other swamp dwellers, including crocodiles, catfish, venomous snakes, and biting flies. This spell reinforces the caster&rsquo;s bond to Bobugbubilz in the eyes of his mortal followers, and with such a bond the caster gains some degree of control over such creatures.</p><br><p><strong>Spell Data:</strong> @Compendium[dcc-core-book.dcc-core-spell-journals.Bottomfeeder Bond]{Bottomfeeder Bond}</p>","results":[{"_id":"TMEHWohJAKB48dGU","flags":{},"type":0,"text":"Lost, failure, and patron taint.","img":"icons/svg/d20-black.svg","resultId":"","weight":1,"range":[-99,1],"drawn":false},{"_id":"fGJ6WVbbMbWtl5Db","flags":{},"type":0,"text":"Lost. Failure.","img":"icons/svg/d20-black.svg","resultId":"","weight":10,"range":[2,11],"drawn":false},{"_id":"ujIuIwp76PHNW6aY","flags":{},"type":0,"text":"Failure, but spell is not lost.","img":"icons/svg/d20-black.svg","resultId":"","weight":4,"range":[12,15],"drawn":false},{"_id":"5I3TGcnXQ0TrMwjB","flags":{},"type":0,"text":"All mundane swampland creatures that come within 30' of the caster regard him with a neutral disposition. Swampland creatures include all amphibians, as well as crocodiles, fish, snakes and other reptiles, insects, and any other mundane creature that lives in a swamp. Intelligent swamp-dwellers, such as lizardmen, receive a Will save to resist the spell effect. If failed, they perceive the caster as non-threatening. The effect continues for 1 turn, or until the caster takes an action that threatens or harms the creatures.","img":"icons/svg/d20-black.svg","resultId":"","weight":2,"range":[16,17],"drawn":false},{"_id":"lEPXZNNJvbW86Ie1","flags":{},"type":0,"text":"As above, except even magical, un-dead, or extra-planar swampland creatures regard the caster as non-threatening. This includes lacedons (water-dwelling ghouls), swamp zombies, witch doctors, scrags (water-dwelling trolls), and primal variants of swamp-dwellers. Intelligent creatures receive a Will save to resist, as above.","img":"icons/svg/d20-black.svg","resultId":"","weight":4,"range":[18,21],"drawn":false},{"_id":"6Libtis7K6zrCY2x","flags":{},"type":0,"text":"As above, and the caster is regarded as non-threatening by all reptilian, amphibian, piscine, and insectoid creatures, as well as the specific swamp-dwelling varieties. Dragons are not considered reptilian for these purposes. Intelligent creatures receive a Will save to resist, as above.","img":"icons/svg/d20-black.svg","resultId":"","weight":2,"range":[22,23],"drawn":false},{"_id":"bYW7cBrP4PaZZiHR","flags":{},"type":0,"text":"As above, and the spell's range is extended to 100'.","img":"icons/svg/d20-black.svg","resultId":"","weight":3,"range":[24,26],"drawn":false},{"_id":"Ez92JblHwgtjtnNX","flags":{},"type":0,"text":"As above, and the spell's duration is extended to 1 hour.","img":"icons/svg/d20-black.svg","resultId":"","weight":5,"range":[27,31],"drawn":false},{"_id":"L8PO4gM9DGrZEtvL","flags":{},"type":0,"text":"All reptilian, amphibian, piscine, and insectoid creatures within 100' regard the caster as not only neutral but potentially as a friend and ally. Unintelligent and mundane creatures of 4 HD or less are automatically affected, while intelligent, magical, and extraplanar creatures, or those of 5 or more HD receive a Will save to resist. Affected creatures hop, slither, and slide to the caster's side in an effort to nuzzle and offer their assistance. The effect lasts for [[/roll 1d6+2]] turns. <br /><br />While under this friendly influence, the creatures obey the caster's commands to the best of their ability (limited by their intelligence and physical capabilities, of course). Creatures sent into dangerous situations or those that oppose their nature receive another Will save at a +4 bonus to break the effect. Examples would include fish ordered out of the water, frogs ordered to fight a creature much larger than themselves, and so on.","img":"icons/svg/d20-black.svg","resultId":"","weight":2,"range":[32,33],"drawn":false},{"_id":"6erA35Q9UEwc5l3M","flags":{},"type":0,"text":"As above, and the effect extends to 200' with a duration of [[/roll 2d6+4]] turns.","img":"icons/svg/d20-black.svg","resultId":"","weight":2,"range":[34,35],"drawn":false},{"_id":"vrLDceFuXT2EV6Na","flags":{},"type":0,"text":"As above, and the effect is ongoing for [[/roll 1d6]] days, to a range of 200'. Creatures affected remain under the spell's influence until its duration ends. By the time the spell ends, the caster is like the Pied Piper of swampland creatures, trailed by a train of crocodiles, snakes, fish, toads, frogs, and tadpoles, along with a veritable cloud of insects. When the effect disperses, this mass of creatures slithers off into the muck.","img":"icons/svg/d20-black.svg","resultId":"","weight":64,"range":[36,99],"drawn":false}],"formula":"1d20","replacement":true,"displayRoll":true}
{"_id":"mABMtBvWbfsGHXxW","name":"Shield Maiden","permission":{"default":0,"U5X07uKi3FMVWkQ1":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.dcc-compendium.spell-tables.5ZkbVOEsrXpPfRKp"}},"img":"modules/dcc-core-book/assets/svg/game-icons-net/swordwoman.svg","description":"<h1>Shield Maiden</h1><p><strong>Level:</strong> 2</p><p><strong>Range:</strong> Self</p><p><strong>Duration:</strong> Varies</p><p><strong>Casting Time:</strong> 1 round</p><p><strong>Save:</strong> None</p><p><strong>Page:</strong> 340</p><br><p>Stumbling across the ruins of a forgotten empire, Sezrekan the Elder discovered a dolmen holding the remains of 50 warrior-maidens. Bending their fierce spirits to his will, he struck a pact with the ghosts permitting him to summon each spirit once. A shield maiden is utterly loyal, interceding on physical attacks against her master, taking damage in his place on any successful attack within 4 points of the caster&rsquo;s target AC. Except as noted below, a maiden cannot attack and stand ready to defend her master in the same round. The death of any shield maiden causes the caster a loss of 1 point of Personality, and all arms and armor vanish upon a maiden&rsquo;s death. In the totality of a campaign, no more than 50 shield maidens can be summoned. Attempting to summon more than a single maiden at the same time causes both to turn on the caster, attacking for [[/roll 1d6]] rounds before vanishing into mist.</p><br><p><strong>Spell Data:</strong> @Compendium[dcc-core-book.dcc-core-spell-journals.Shield Maiden]{Shield Maiden}</p>","results":[{"_id":"N54mXDKc9oLHufyg","flags":{},"type":0,"text":"Lost, failure, and patron taint.","img":"icons/svg/d20-black.svg","resultId":"","weight":1,"range":[-99,1],"drawn":false},{"_id":"fcis10kL846a8vZ2","flags":{},"type":0,"text":"Lost. Failure.","img":"icons/svg/d20-black.svg","resultId":"","weight":10,"range":[2,11],"drawn":false},{"_id":"PbhoStmT2ecJAyqR","flags":{},"type":0,"text":"Failure, but spell is not lost.","img":"icons/svg/d20-black.svg","resultId":"","weight":2,"range":[12,13],"drawn":false},{"_id":"DFS4AogU5KVTNk7O","flags":{},"type":0,"text":"A shield maiden appears with stats as a level 1 warrior, 10 hp, and mundane equipment. The maiden serves for 1 hour before vanishing into mist, freed from her indenture.","img":"icons/svg/d20-black.svg","resultId":"","weight":2,"range":[14,15],"drawn":false},{"_id":"xEA9uo2f4ila74UD","flags":{},"type":0,"text":"A shield-maiden appears with stats as a level 2 warrior, 15 hp, and mundane equipment. The maiden serves for 1 day before vanishing into mist, freed from her indenture.","img":"icons/svg/d20-black.svg","resultId":"","weight":4,"range":[16,19],"drawn":false},{"_id":"4eF35UAk30XcPvHK","flags":{},"type":0,"text":"A shield maiden appears with stats as a level 3 warrior, 20 hp, and mundane equipment. The maiden bears a kite shield, granting +1 to her master's AC against ranged attacks and +1 to saves against physical damage. The maiden serves for 1 week before vanishing into mist, freed from her indenture.","img":"icons/svg/d20-black.svg","resultId":"","weight":2,"range":[20,21],"drawn":false},{"_id":"rTfmtuMNRps2ZjbW","flags":{},"type":0,"text":"A shield maiden appears with stats as a level 4 warrior, normal ability scores, 25 hp, and armed with a +1 spear. The maiden bears a great shield, granting +2 to her master's AC, +3 vs. ranged attacks and +2 to saves against physical damage. The maiden serves for 1 month before vanishing into mist, freed from her indenture.","img":"icons/svg/d20-black.svg","resultId":"","weight":4,"range":[22,25],"drawn":false},{"_id":"Jy1RNcYTvbZXOHJi","flags":{},"type":0,"text":"A shield maiden appears with stats as a level 4 warrior, one exceptional ability score, 25 hp, and armed with a +2 spear. The maiden bears a great shield, granting +2 to her master's AC, +3 vs. ranged attacks and +2 to saves against physical damage. <br /><br />Any time a physical attack succeeds against her master, the shield maiden can make an immediate counterattack against foe that struck her master. The maiden serves for 1 year before vanishing into mist, freed from her indenture.","img":"icons/svg/d20-black.svg","resultId":"","weight":4,"range":[26,29],"drawn":false},{"_id":"FdboFaJ7Loy2LJkO","flags":{},"type":0,"text":"A shield maiden appears with stats as a level 5 warrior, two exceptional ability scores, 30 hp, and armed with a +2 spear. The maiden bears a great shield, granting +2 to her master's AC, +3 vs. ranged attacks, and +2 to saves against physical damage. Any time a physical attack succeeds against her master, the shield maiden can make an immediate counterattack against foe that struck her master. The maiden serves for 1 year before vanishing into mist, freed from her indenture.","img":"icons/svg/d20-black.svg","resultId":"","weight":2,"range":[30,31],"drawn":false},{"_id":"iN6AHoFQ4owrtEJo","flags":{},"type":0,"text":"A shield maiden appears with stats as a level 6 warrior, three exceptional ability scores, 35 hp, armed with a +2 spear, astride a pegasus. The maiden bears a great shield, granting +2 to her master's AC, +3 vs. ranged attacks, and +2 to saves against physical damage. <br /><br />Any time a physical attack succeeds against her master, the shield maiden can make an immediate counterattack against foe that struck her master. The maiden serves for 10 years before vanishing into mist, freed from her indenture.","img":"icons/svg/d20-black.svg","resultId":"","weight":2,"range":[32,33],"drawn":false},{"_id":"qcwMSSLRfLuF32Yi","flags":{},"type":0,"text":"A shield maiden appears with stats as a level 7 warrior, four exceptional ability scores, 50 hp, and armed with a +2 spear, astride a pegasus. The maiden bears a +1 great shield, granting +3 to her master's AC, +4 vs. ranged attacks, and +3 to saves against physical damage. <br /><br />Any time a physical attack succeeds against her master, the shield maiden can make an immediate counterattack against foe that struck her master. The maiden serves for the remainder of her master's life. Upon the caster's death, she vanishes into mist, freed from her indenture.","img":"icons/svg/d20-black.svg","resultId":"","weight":66,"range":[34,99],"drawn":false}],"formula":"1d20","replacement":true,"displayRoll":true}
{"_id":"nUW4Jc3GzfHON3wx","name":"Invoke the King of Elfland","permission":{"default":0,"wWErSsSXezizF0nw":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.dcc-compendiums.dcc-spell-tables.BtBBCySOQLD8njSZ"}},"img":"modules/dcc-core-book/assets/svg/game-icons-net/forest.svg","description":"<h1>Invoke the King of Elfland</h1><p><strong>Level:</strong> 1</p><p><strong>Range:</strong> Self</p><p><strong>Duration:</strong> Varies</p><p><strong>Casting Time:</strong> 1 round, and the spell may be cast only a limited number of times, according to results of patron bond.</p><p><strong>Save:</strong> None</p><p><strong>Page:</strong> 342</p><br><p>Master of the verdant realm glimpsed only through sun-dappled groves, the mist of great waterfalls, and the moments of dusk and dawn, the King of Elfland rules all elf-kin from his throne of mist and ice. Fierce once roused, the white-bearded regent keeps watch over the dreaming land, protecting against incursion. He grants fearsome powers to his mortal champions, but can often seem fickle and sanguine, neglecting affairs not immediately pertaining to the Elflands.</p><br><p><strong>Spell Data:</strong> @Compendium[dcc-core-book.dcc-core-spell-journals.Invoke the King of Elfland]{Invoke the King of Elfland}</p>","results":[{"_id":"8Ev36hLB0wZjpSIY","flags":{},"type":0,"text":"Lost, failure, and worse! Roll [[/roll 1d6]] modified by Luck: (3 or less) corruption + patron taint; (4-5) corruption; (6+) patron taint.","img":"icons/svg/d20-black.svg","resultId":"","weight":1,"range":[-99,1],"drawn":false},{"_id":"C1cMINL5jiu46BqD","flags":{},"type":0,"text":"Failure. Unlike other spells, invoke patron may not be lost for the day. Depending on the results of patron bond, the wizard may still be able to cast it.","img":"icons/svg/d20-black.svg","resultId":"","weight":1,"range":[2,11],"drawn":false},{"_id":"Akubdjt4s7EMlz8N","flags":{},"type":0,"text":"The King of Elfland answers the petitioner's plea, but is quickly distracted by other matters. The caster receives +4 to his next attack, saving throw, skill check, or spell check.","img":"icons/svg/d20-black.svg","resultId":"","weight":1,"range":[12,13],"drawn":false},{"_id":"VEs0pjpKSuJNMuEz","flags":{},"type":0,"text":"The caster's weapons are endowed with the slumbering magic of Elfland. For the next [[/roll 1d5]]+CL rounds, targets struck by the caster's weapons must succeed on a DC 10+CL Will save or succumb to magical sleep (duration [[/roll 1d6]] hours; can only be roused by violent shaking for [[/roll 1d4]] rounds). The magic is associated with the caster's weapons not the caster; while the magic persists, another character may attack with these weapons to gain the same benefit.","img":"icons/svg/d20-black.svg","resultId":"","weight":1,"range":[14,17],"drawn":false},{"_id":"MCaEYyz9n5yuL1N0","flags":{},"type":0,"text":"For [[/roll 1d4]]+CL rounds, the caster fades from existence, becoming a mere shadow suspended between the fae realms and the mortal lands. His AC and Ref saves improve by +2, and with a successful Will save (DC 10), the caster can turn invisible. If the caster critically fails the Will save by rolling a natural 1, he delves too far into the Elflands, vanishing into the fae realms, never to return.","img":"icons/svg/d20-black.svg","resultId":"","weight":1,"range":[18,19],"drawn":false},{"_id":"c6cqrVt5Y9M3b8Vm","flags":{},"type":0,"text":"The King of Elfland grants the caster a chance to step back in time [[/roll 1d6]]+CL rounds. This does not automatically change the flow of events that has already happened; the caster is a visible observer who can interact with those events, even watching his own 'past self' perform activities in the recent past. The caster may be able to prevent some recent event from occurring, aid in an attack that would otherwise have missed, or shout a warning.","img":"icons/svg/d20-black.svg","resultId":"","weight":1,"range":[20,23],"drawn":false},{"_id":"dGGEk5T33odqyhOb","flags":{},"type":0,"text":"The caster's weapons are enchanted with the wrothful magic of Elfland. For the next [[/roll 1d4]]+CL rounds, targets struck by the caster's weapons must succeed on a DC 10+CL Will save or vanish into Elfland, returning to the mortal plane some [[/roll 5d100]] years later. <br /><br />Immortals and other extraplanar creatures (at the judge's discretion) may be immune to the caster's dread magics. The magic is associated with the caster's weapons not the caster; while the magic persists, another character may attack with these weapons to gain the same benefit.","img":"icons/svg/d20-black.svg","resultId":"","weight":1,"range":[24,27],"drawn":false},{"_id":"fiY0TGuJf2sstBuZ","flags":{},"type":0,"text":"The King of Elfland grants the caster a chance to step back in time [[/roll 1d6]]+CL hours. This does not change the flow of events that has already happened; the caster is a visible observer who can interact with those events, even watching his own 'past self' perform activities in the recent past. The caster may be able to prevent some recent event from occurring, aid in an attack that would otherwise have missed, or shout a warning.","img":"icons/svg/d20-black.svg","resultId":"","weight":1,"range":[28,29],"drawn":false},{"_id":"EnKV5gTuTEYFyGPP","flags":{},"type":0,"text":"The caster becomes a shining sylvan paladin in the service of Elfland. For [[/roll 1d8]]+CL rounds, the caster and three allies of his choosing receive +4 to AC and all saving throws, +3 to all attacks, spell check and damage rolls, and automatically succeed on any Recovering the Body checks.","img":"icons/svg/d20-black.svg","resultId":"","weight":1,"range":[30,31],"drawn":false},{"_id":"ZvLrynjguA4l81sB","flags":{},"type":0,"text":"The King of Elfland anoints the caster as his champion. For [[/roll 1d12]]+CL rounds, the caster and five allies of his choosing receive +6 to AC and all saving throws, +5 to all attacks, spell check and damage rolls, and automatically succeed on any Recovering the Body checks. Even if one of the characters is somehow slain, he simply slips into the sylvan realms where he is healed by elven maids, returning to the mortal realms [[/roll 1d3]] days later, healed in both body and soul.","img":"icons/svg/d20-black.svg","resultId":"","weight":1,"range":[32,99],"drawn":false}],"formula":"1d20","replacement":true,"displayRoll":true}
{"_id":"nkEqE8FHsTyt7nmZ","name":"The Dreaming","permission":{"default":0,"U5X07uKi3FMVWkQ1":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.dcc-compendium.spell-tables.ao6lQLlq3g74jYkH"}},"img":"modules/dcc-core-book/assets/svg/game-icons-net/dream-catcher.svg","description":"<h1>The Dreaming</h1><p><strong>Level:</strong> 3</p><p><strong>Range:</strong> Self</p><p><strong>Duration:</strong> Varies</p><p><strong>Casting Time:</strong> 1 day</p><p><strong>Save:</strong> None</p><p><strong>Page:</strong> 347</p><br><p>The caster calls upon the ancient, slumbering magic of the Elflands. Time slows as the fey dreaming of twilight and dusk ooze into the mortal realms.</p><br><p><strong>Spell Data:</strong> @Compendium[dcc-core-book.dcc-core-spell-journals.The Dreaming]{The Dreaming}</p>","results":[{"_id":"lgVKpn4SbKkKpSdA","flags":{},"type":0,"text":"Lost, failure, and patron taint.","img":"icons/svg/d20-black.svg","resultId":"","weight":1,"range":[-99,1],"drawn":false},{"_id":"PUAsmRY7EgG8Mpdt","flags":{},"type":0,"text":"Lost. Failure.","img":"icons/svg/d20-black.svg","resultId":"","weight":10,"range":[2,11],"drawn":false},{"_id":"VKwsSRxjBKHtA80c","flags":{},"type":0,"text":"Failure, but spell is not lost.","img":"icons/svg/d20-black.svg","resultId":"","weight":4,"range":[12,15],"drawn":false},{"_id":"AnRQKGp5EXX2VRY1","flags":{},"type":0,"text":"The dreaming magic of the faerie-realms spills into the world around the caster, slowing the passage of time. Versed in the ways of the Elflands, the caster may take an extra action each round and is granted a +1 bonus to his AC, Reflex saves, and attack rolls. The extra action is at the caster's lowest action die. The enchantment lasts for [[/roll 1d4]] rounds.","img":"icons/svg/d20-black.svg","resultId":"","weight":2,"range":[16,17],"drawn":false},{"_id":"8aOX96W2rDv8F2uv","flags":{},"type":0,"text":"The caster's mastery of the Elflands is like an aura, protecting his allies from the fey and fell magics. The caster and all his allies within 50' may take an extra action each round (at each character's lowest action die) and are granted a +1 bonus to AC, Reflex saves, and attack rolls. The enchantment lasts for [[/roll 1d4]] rounds.","img":"icons/svg/d20-black.svg","resultId":"","weight":4,"range":[18,21],"drawn":false},{"_id":"9tJlshw2EoVE76iS","flags":{},"type":0,"text":"Time slows to a crawl. The caster and all his allies within 50' may take two extra actions each round (at each character's lowest action die) and are granted a +2 bonus to AC, Reflex saves, and attack rolls. The enchantment lasts for [[/roll 1d3]] rounds.","img":"icons/svg/d20-black.svg","resultId":"","weight":2,"range":[22,23],"drawn":false},{"_id":"q643epycCkCXfroB","flags":{},"type":0,"text":"The caster and all his allies within 50' may take three extra actions each round (at each character's lowest action die) and are granted a +3 bonus to AC, Reflex saves, and attack rolls. The enchantment lasts for [[/roll 1d3]] rounds.","img":"icons/svg/d20-black.svg","resultId":"","weight":3,"range":[24,26],"drawn":false},{"_id":"XxXQSqpGH2QEFO7x","flags":{},"type":0,"text":"The caster and all his allies within 50' may take three extra actions each round (at each character's lowest action die) and are granted a +3 bonus to AC, Reflex saves, and attack rolls. The enchantment lasts for [[/roll 1d3]] rounds, and may be extended with spellburn. <br /><br />When the spell is about to expire, the caster may spellburn 1 point of attribute to extend the spell's effect by 1 round. He may continue to extend the spell's effect, round by round, in this manner. Using such spellburn requires an action on the caster's part (which can be one of several actions provided he extends the spell).","img":"icons/svg/d20-black.svg","resultId":"","weight":5,"range":[27,31],"drawn":false},{"_id":"OJMawLtROfW7JHRF","flags":{},"type":0,"text":"The passage of time stops for [[/roll 1d3]]+CL rounds. The caster is the sole mortal immune to the effects of the enchantment, though gods and other immortals may also be immune. During this time, the caster may take normal activations, while other creatures are frozen in time. This can allow the caster to cast multiple spells, make multiple attacks, flee, or otherwise do whatever he wishes with no chance for others to react.","img":"icons/svg/d20-black.svg","resultId":"","weight":2,"range":[32,33],"drawn":false},{"_id":"MFF9GESrhf6w27Js","flags":{},"type":0,"text":"Time stops, resuming only when the caster or the King of Elfland dismiss the enchantment. The caster is the sole mortal immune to the effects of the enchantment, though gods and other immortals may also be immune. During this time, the caster may take normal activations, while other creatures are frozen in time. This can allow the caster to cast multiple spells, make multiple attacks, flee, or otherwise do whatever he wishes with no chance for others to react.","img":"icons/svg/d20-black.svg","resultId":"","weight":2,"range":[34,35],"drawn":false},{"_id":"iZooyWL7IdpU7DVv","flags":{},"type":0,"text":"Time stops, as result 34-35 above. Additionally, the caster may turn back time by permanently spellburning attribute points at the rate of 2 points for every 10 minutes.","img":"icons/svg/d20-black.svg","resultId":"","weight":64,"range":[36,99],"drawn":false}],"formula":"1d20","replacement":true,"displayRoll":true}
