{"_id":"ydDDkc4X0dP2FVnS","name":"Warp and Weft","permission":{"default":0,"U5X07uKi3FMVWkQ1":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.dcc-compendium.spell-tables.4TS6UhlI64bmD5EU"}},"img":"modules/dcc-core-book/assets/svg/game-icons-net/rolled-cloth.svg","description":"<h1>Warp and Weft</h1><p><strong>Level:</strong> 3</p><p><strong>Range:</strong> [[/roll 1d100]]' +10' per CL</p><p><strong>Duration:</strong> [[/roll 1d3]]+CL turns *</p><p><strong>Casting Time:</strong> 2 rounds</p><p><strong>Save:</strong> Will save vs. spell check if unwilling</p><p><strong>Page:</strong> 353</p><br><p>Servant to the Three Fates, the caster can bend, stretch&mdash;and in rare instances&mdash; weave the threads of destiny that rule the universe. Such power always comes with great risk, and even the caster&rsquo;s masters are loath to alter what has already been decided. Once cast, the spell effect can be declared at any time, regardless of initiative order. Each time the spell is unsuccessfully cast there is a cumulative 1% chance that the caster winks from existence, never to return. If the caster elects to turn the spell&rsquo;s effects on himself, he must first attempt a&nbsp; Will save vs. spell check or immediately cease to exist.</p><br><p><strong>Spell Data:</strong> @Compendium[dcc-core-book.dcc-core-spell-journals.Warp and Weft]{Warp and Weft}</p>","results":[{"_id":"LbnWe3zlW0Sb0VaV","flags":{},"type":0,"text":"Lost, failure, and patron taint.","img":"icons/svg/d20-black.svg","resultId":"","weight":1,"range":[-99,1],"drawn":false},{"_id":"gN9IAqRRiX25WqwX","flags":{},"type":0,"text":"Lost. Failure.","img":"icons/svg/d20-black.svg","resultId":"","weight":10,"range":[2,11],"drawn":false},{"_id":"RJAvXHhyZCLCLpcB","flags":{},"type":0,"text":"Failure, but spell is not lost.","img":"icons/svg/d20-black.svg","resultId":"","weight":4,"range":[12,15],"drawn":false},{"_id":"4xcTPnCNeghvUdOt","flags":{},"type":0,"text":"The caster can alter a single saving throw, ensuring that a